===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{context|countable|lang=en}} A [[specific]] act committed in [[violation]] of the [[law]].
# {{context|uncountable|lang=en}} The [[practice]] or [[habit]] of [[commit]]ting crimes.
#: '''''Crime''' doesn’t pay.''
# {{context|uncountable|lang=en}} [[criminal]] [[acts]] collectively.
# Any great wickedness or sin; iniquity.
#* Alexander Pope
#*: No '''crime''' was thine, if 'tis no '''crime''' to love.
# {{context|obsolete|lang=en}} That which occasions crime.
#* Spenser
#*: the tree of life, the '''crime''' of our first father's fall

